<body style="max-width:800px;margin:40px auto;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;">
  <h1>VRoomie – Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> December 8, 2025</p>
  <p><strong>App Name:</strong> VRoomie – #1 Remote Car Health Check-Up</p>
  <p><strong>Owner:</strong> DGeorgeA</p>

  <p>VRoomie (“we”, “our”, or “us”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the VRoomie mobile application.</p>

  <h2>1. Age Restriction</h2>
  <p>VRoomie is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect, solicit, or store any personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that information has been collected from a child under 13, we will promptly delete it.</p>

  <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>VRoomie is designed to operate with minimal data collection.</p>

  <h3>Audio Data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>The app records engine sound only when you explicitly start a recording.</li>
    <li>Audio is used solely for diagnostic analysis.</li>
    <li>Audio is not recorded in the background.</li>
    <li>Audio is not used for advertising or profiling.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Device Information</h3>
  <p>We may automatically receive limited non-personal technical information, such as device type, operating system version, and app performance diagnostics. This data is used strictly for improving stability and performance.</p>

  <h3>No Personal Identity Required</h3>
  <p>You are not required to create an account. We do not collect names, email addresses, phone numbers, or precise location.</p>

  <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>Recorded audio and technical data are used only to analyze engine sound, detect mechanical anomalies, display diagnostic results, and improve app accuracy and reliability. We do not sell, rent, or share your data for advertising.</p>

  <h2>4. Data Storage & Security</h2>
  <p>Diagnostic audio may be temporarily processed for analysis. Admin-uploaded sound patterns are stored securely. We apply reasonable security safeguards to protect data. No continuous background monitoring occurs.</p>

  <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>VRoomie may use secure third-party cloud services only for necessary technical operations, such as audio file storage and system performance monitoring. These services follow industry-standard security practices.</p>

  <h2>6. User Control</h2>
  <p>You have full control over when recordings start and stop, which sessions are saved, and when data is deleted. You may delete your stored sessions directly from within the app.</p>

  <h2>7. Cookies & Tracking</h2>
  <p>VRoomie does not use cookies for advertising and does not perform cross-app tracking.</p>

  <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted within the app or on our official webpage. The Effective Date will be updated accordingly.</p>

  <h2>9. Contact Information</h2>
  <p>Email: support@vroomie.app<br/>
     Developer: DGeorgeA</p>

  <p>By using VRoomie, you agree to this Privacy Policy.</p>
